The paper presents a method for training a social robot to generate backchannels during human-robot interaction using reinforcement learning. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the problem of engagement in human-robot interaction, which is a topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The method involves processing speech activity, which could fall under natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper uses deep Q-networks for reinforcement learning, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
